<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="U" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Unwilling" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Unwilling,</orth> 1) not willing, disinclined, reluctant: <bibl n="shak. ven 365" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 365</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 309" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 309</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 1, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 61</bibl>. R2 <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 3</bibl>, <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 3</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.240" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 240</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.60" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 60</bibl>.<lb />2) undesigned, involuntary: <cit><quote>and being opened, threw u. light upon the wide wound,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1051" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1051</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>'twas a fault u.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 159</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>